Tumeric Lemon Loaf
  --Dan Churchill, My Fitness Pal
  
Bread:
2 c flour (ap, almond, or oat)
2 lemons, zest and juice
1 c olive oil
2/3 c maple syrup
2 eggs
2 bananas, mashed
pinch of salt
1 1/2 tsp baking powder
1 tbsp tumeric


Preheat oven to 350F; grease a loaf pan. Combine oil and syrup in a bowl. Whisk in one egg at a time and mix until thoroughly combined. Add in bananas and mix. In a separate bowl combine the flour, zest, salt, baking powder and tumeric. Add lemon juice to wet, mix to combine. Then combine wet and dry, mix well. Pour into prepared pan and bake for 35-40 min, until tester inserted comes out clean. Let cool for 5 min before removing from pan.


Glaze:
2 lemons, zested and juiced
2/3 c maple syrup
1 c olive oil
 
Pout all ingredients into a saucepan and stir over medium heat. Cook until it reduces 1/3, set aside and let cool while bread bakes. Once loaf is out of pan, can drizzle over the top




Notes: Can use coconut oil or butter in place of olive oil. Also can sub other sweeteners for maple syrup
